  "title": "Senior Executive (Academic & Residential Experience)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Scope:</strong><br />- Student Community Engagement (ARE) programme/project administration including project applications, claim submissions/reimbursements and reporting.</p><p>-Manage clubs and hall council purchases and asset procurement & management</p><p>- Maintenance of Student Community Engagement databases and the preparation of management and other reporting requirements.</p><p>- Support the development and communication of ARE publicity materials and     maintenance of its publicity portals.</p><p>- Manage facilities booking requests</p><p>- Support other ARE administrative requirements as assigned e.g., meeting     arrangements, meeting minutes, support at SAO events etc.</p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong><br />- Degree/ Diploma in any discipline. Fresh school leavers are welcomed to apply.<br />- Candidates with 1-2 years of experience in supporting programme/project administration including processing of programme budgets, funding claims/reimbursements and reporting requirements would have an added advantage<br />- Proficient in all Microsoft applications especially Excel and Power Automate.<br />- Highly organised and meticulous.<br />- Able do forward planning, anticipate needs, with a strong initiative to take ownership of tasks assigned and make appropriate recommendations<br />- Ability to effectively manage multi-task concurrently and adapt to changes well.</p><p><strong>Working Hours: </strong>Office Hours <br /><strong>Contract Period: </strong>1 year</p><p><strong>Salary: </strong>$3200-$3500/month</p><p><strong>Location:</strong> Nanyang Avenue (West)</p><p>EA License No.: 96C4864</p><p>Reg No.: R26159658 BRANN LEONG CHUN HOE </p>",
